text: Sigrid Wienke (born July 1949) is an East German former long track speed skater, who was active in the 1960s and early 1970s.Saisonauftakt für Eisflitzer, Neues Deutschland, 09 November 1968 Wienke represented her nation at the World Allround Speed Skating Championships for Women in 1965, finishing 28th overall.Jugend läuft um Titel, Neues Deutschland, 20 February 1965Woronina getipt as favoriete voor titel bij de schaatsmeisjes, Nieuwe Schiedamsche Courant, 5 February 1965, p.7 She also competed at other international competitions. Between 1965 and 1971 she competed at 19 national championships (different disciplines per year), winning a total of two silver and three bronze medals. == Records== === Personal records === ==References== Category:1949 births Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Date of birth missing (living people) Category:Female speed skaters Category:East German sportswomen Category:Living people
